title: Trump plans Iowa stop in Burlington
text:
Trump plans Iowa stop in Burlington Charly Haley , chaley@dmreg.com 9:14 p.m. CDT October 16, 2015 Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump speaks during a campaign stop at the Electric Park Ballroom, Wednesday, Oct. 7, 2015, in Waterloo, Iowa. (Photo: Charlie Neibergall/Associated Press) 
GOP presidential candidate Donald Trump will return to Iowa next week for a rally in Burlington. 
The Republican front-runner's "Make America Great Again Rally" will be at 6 p.m. Oct. 21 in the Burlington Memorial Auditorium, 200 Front Street, according to an email from his campaign. 
Doors open at 4:30 p.m. Click here for ticket information . Read or Share this story: http://dmreg.co/1RNwQxP TOP VIDEOS
